sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor User
    participant Skill as peer-review<br/>(skill)
    participant Git as git / gh
    participant SecScan as Secret Scanner<br/>(Step 4b)
    participant Reviewer as Reviewer<br/>(self / claude-*)
    participant CLI as External CLI<br/>(copilot/codex/gemini)
    participant Triage as Triage Subagent<br/>(Step 4f)

    User->>Skill: /peer-review [target] [--model M] [--focus T]

    %% Step 1
    Skill->>Skill: Parse & validate $ARGUMENTS<br/>(regex check $PR / $BRANCH / $FOCUS)

    %% Step 2 — collect content
    rect rgb(240,248,255)
        Note over Skill,Git: Step 2 — Collect content
        alt --staged / auto-detected staged
            Skill->>Git: git diff --staged
            Git-->>Skill: diff bytes
        else --branch NAME
            Skill->>Git: detect default branch, then<br/>git diff DEFAULT...BRANCH
            Git-->>Skill: diff bytes
        else --pr N
            Skill->>Git: gh pr view --json ... + gh pr diff
            Git-->>Skill: PR meta (title/body) + diff bytes
        else path
            Skill->>Skill: Read / Glob (no shell)<br/>collect file contents
        end
    end

    %% Step 3 — template
    Skill->>Skill: Select prompt template<br/>(diff vs consistency) + --focus

    %% Step 4 — dispatch
    rect rgb(245,255,245)
        Note over Skill,Triage: Step 4 — Spawn reviewer
        alt model = self or claude-*
            Skill->>Reviewer: prompt + <untrusted_*> wrapped content
            Reviewer-->>Skill: findings (or NO FINDINGS)
        else external CLI (copilot/codex/gemini)
            Skill->>SecScan: Step 4b — regex scan $PROMPT for secrets
            alt secret pattern hit
                SecScan-->>User: show redacted context,<br/>prompt [y/N]
                User-->>SecScan: y (or abort → cleanup + exit)
            end
            Skill->>Skill: 4c — write prompt to mktemp file<br/>(mode 600, single bash call)
            Skill->>CLI: 4d — invoke via stdin redirect<br/>(--allow-all-tools --deny-tool=write / etc.)
            CLI-->>Skill: raw review output
            Skill->>Skill: rm -f $PROMPT_FILE
            Skill->>Skill: 4e — parse → normalized findings<br/>(severity map)
            Skill->>Triage: 4f — classify each finding<br/>(recommend / skip)
            Triage-->>Skill: per-finding decisions
        end
    end

    %% Step 5 — present
    Skill-->>User: ## Peer Review — [target] ([model])<br/>findings grouped by severity<br/>+ triage-skipped (S1, S2...)
    Skill-->>User: Apply prompt [all/1,2/1,S1/skip]<br/>(final message, stop generating)

    %% Step 6 — apply
    User->>Skill: all | 1,3,S1 | skip
    alt apply selection
        Skill->>Skill: Edit files for chosen findings
        Skill-->>User: per-change report
    else skip
        Skill-->>User: Skipped N findings. No changes made.
    end

    opt target was --pr N
        Skill-->>User: PR URL (mandatory last line)
    end
